snippet.textDisplay:
Absolute disaster. If this is the best Labour can offer as a "credible" opposition to hold the government to account, then our democracy is in real trouble. And don't get me started on RLB, a deer in the headlights during every interview. Also, Keir "don't called me Sir" Starmer as the favourite to win it? This is a man who is backed by Blair and Mandleson, which in itself attached a bad smell to his leadership bid and possibly reign.
The only ones i could see as credible options for Labour to attempt to stabilise, is Lisa Nandy, or Ian Lavery. Both supporters of Brexit, and could heal the divides in those northern heartlands. Labour supporters can't seem to understand how dire these election results were. Practically wiped out in Scotland, lost its heartlands, lost safe seats that became marginals that will flip blue eventually, and we are left with a Labour Party who will never see a Labour majority ever again. The people have spoken, and Labour have been punished for their sins against the working classes.
And let's not forget about JP, a woman who laughed and mocked the idea of a discussion talking about men's issues. A vile human being in my eyes for doing that. Are we really going to let someone like that become leader of this country.
